#stance=stance1
#originalStanceText=After Conception
#originalTopic=when-does-life-begin
  Nature doesn't just dispose of unused sperm and eggs. Miscarriage, gets rid of fetus that have started to develop. Many species of animals have large numbers of off spring. Which aren't meant to reach maturity.   So until a fetus has fully developed, and is viable. I don't think we should call it life.   We got to draw the line some where. For legal purposes.    Nature doesn't work that well for us; when left to itself. 